text: Mads Mensah Larsen (born 12 August 1991) is a Danish handball player for Rhein-Neckar Löwen and the Denmark national team. He has played for the clubs AG København, Nordsjælland Håndbold and Aalborg Håndbold. He was born in Holbæk, Denmark. He won a gold medal at the 2016 Summer Olympics. In March 2020, Larsen tested positive for COVID-19 during the 2020 coronavirus pandemic.Mads Mensah Larsen er smittet med coronavirus ==References== Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Olympic gold medalists for Denmark Category:Handball players
